==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Otaheite apple
<hw>O`ta*hei"te ap"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So named from
<etsep>Otaheite</etsep>, or Tahiti, one of the Society Islands.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The fruit of a Polynesian
anacardiaceous tree (<spn>Spondias dulcis</spn>), also called
<altname>vi-apple</altname>. It is rather larger than an apple, and the
rind has a flavor of turpentine, but the flesh is said to taste like
pineapples.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A West Indian name for a myrtaceous
tree (<spn>Jambosa Malaccensis</spn>) which bears crimson
berries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Otalgia</ent>⟦br⟧
